[1] Mali: confirms 8th case
Date: 24 Nov 2014
Source: Associated Press [edited]
http://abcnews.go.com/Health/wireStory/mali-confirms-eighth-ebola-case-27145797


Mali has confirmed a new case of Ebola, bringing to 8 the number of people who have fallen ill with the deadly disease in the West African country. A government statement issued Monday night [24 Nov 2014] said the patient had been placed in a treatment center. All of Mali's Ebola cases can be traced back to a 70-year-old imam who was brought to the country from Guinea, where the epidemic 1st began; 6 of Mali's 8 Ebola patients have died. The government said Sat [22 Nov 2014] that another patient who tested positive was also receiving treatment and had been isolated. Officials are monitoring 271 people in a bid to contain the disease... - more

