******
[2] Sierra Leone: Italian doctor repatriated
Date: 24 Nov 2014
Source: Reuters [edited]
http://www.reuters.com/article/2014/11/24/us-health-ebola-italy-idUSKCN0J80VA20141124


An Italian doctor who contracted Ebola while working in Sierra Leone is being flown to Italy, the Health Ministry in Rome said on Mon [24 Nov 2014]. The ministry said the doctor, who had been working for the humanitarian group Emergency, was in a stable condition and was eating and drinking on his own. He is expected to arrive on Monday night and will be treated in the Lazzaro Spallanzani infectious diseases institute in Rome, the ministry said.

[Byline: Antonella Cinelli]

